</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/bquelliousquaterstherebirth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=impudent>impudent</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Uber guild basher <br><font color=blue>QC Supporter</span><br>  Posts: 383<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(12/6/02 4:28:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=725.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lewt Rules?</span><hr size=1> Let's see if I can help ya some.<br>
<br>
Points systems suck for new players.<br>
<br>
NBG systems suck for old players.<br>
<br>
Officer vote suck for players that piss off the officers (<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :cuss --><img src=http://www.gamers-forums.com/smilies/contrib/edoom/cussing.gif ALT=":cuss"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).<br>
<br>
My best advice to you is the adjust your loot structure based on the NEEDS of your guild as a collective, along with your activities.<br>
<br>
IE.. if you feel you are lacking in DPS, go raid some nice weapon spots.. etc etc.<br>
<br>
Always remember.. everyone deserves SOMETHING from EVERY raid...  be it a BOC, SoD or just a plain &quot;thanks for coming&quot;.  It takes a groups effort, don't JUST thanks the winners of the loot. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=198804">Impudent Blasphemy</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
