</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub54.ezboard.com/bquelliousquaterstherebirth.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tunset>Tunset</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.animatedgif.net/violent/mranischw_e0.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=blue>Professional Thread Derailer</font><br>Woooooooooooooooo!<br><span style=background:red>I like monkeys</span></span><br>  Posts: 121<br> <font color=#00CCFF>(12/6/02 10:14:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub54.ezboard.com/fquelliousquaterstherebirthfrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=725.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Lewt Rules?</span><hr size=1> Starting out a new guild is a tough thing to do....<br>
<br>
There are things that you need to accomplish if you want to advance as a guild.<br>
<br>
The first thing being, you need to outfit a tank.  Having a main tank that can stand up to damage of an uber mob is critical.<br>
<br>
Even though Wraith is on a points system now, we started on an officer award system.<br>
<br>
This is probably the best way to start out a new guild.<br>
<br>
The most important reason being that you can outfit the people that you know will be the biggest assets to the guild the best.<br>
<br>
If you do not have a main tank that can handle the high end mobs, then you will limit the advancement of the guild as a whole.<br>
<br>
My suggestion is that you go on an officer award system to begin with and then advance from there.  That way you can insure that the early awards will benefit the guild as a whole.<br>
